# What is Patch Tuesday for Windows and When is it?

Microsoft’s “Patch Tuesday” occurs on the second Tuesday of each month. This is the day when, like clockwork, Microsoft releases large update packages for Windows.As Microsoft patches security vulnerabilities, it doesn’t release those patches immediately.Microsoft does this to make the update process as predictable as possible for administrators. IT professionals know that patches will arrive on the second Tuesday of each month.Microsoft doesn’t have a guaranteed time these patches and Microsoft’s information bulletins about them will be released.
